title: South West Secret Agents by Laura Quigley (.epub)
description:
South West Secret Agents: True Stories of the West Country at War by Laura Quigley

Requirements: ePUB Reader, 6.6MB

Genre: Non-fiction | History

Overview: 

Thrilling true tales of Second World War spies from across the West Country have been collected together for the very first time in this fascinating book. From the rescue operations during the exodus from France to the secret guerrilla army in Devon and Cornwall, this book will amaze and intrigue with the incredible stories of Pip Jarvis, Jasper Lawn of N51, the Helford Flotilla, the Motor Torpedo Boats from Dartmouth, and the first escape routes for POWs, agents and crashed airmen
